schema.description: A spot insertion for playing a series of spots when a cue is received during a program.

createdDate.description: The date and time the spot insertion was created. Generated at creation.

cue.description: The cue that triggers the spot insertion.

endDate.description: The date the spot insertion ends. The time will be set to midnight Eastern Time.

id.description: The unique ID of the spot insertion. Generated at creation.

spots.description: The ordered list of spot IDs to play.

startDate.description: The date the spot insertion can start. The time will be set to midnight Eastern Time.

schema.description: An electronic program guide (EPG) batch operation to create or update metadata on one or more guide programs.

createdDate.description: The date and time the batch was created.

finishedDate.description: The date and time the batch finished (either successful or failed).

format.description: The format of the metadata file defining the create or update actions to be performed on one or more EPG programs.

message.description: The human readable success or failure message.

name.description: The optional name of the batch for human reference.

program.description: The program information to associate the ingested metadata with. This is only required if the metadata format doesn't provide the program title and air date information directly. If this is specified, it will overrite the value specfified in the metadata file. If this is specified, the metadata file should only contain one program.

airDate.description: The airDate for the program in ISO 8601 format.

status.description: The current processing status.

uri.description: The URI to the metadata file defining the batch creates/updates.
